==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] ''[[Μακεδονία]]'' (Makedonia) highland, from ''[[μακεδνός]]'' (makednos), high, tall, from [[Doric Greek]] ''[[μάκος]]'' (makos), height, length; in [[Ionian Greek]]: ''[[μήκος]]'' (mekos). In Greek mythology, ''[[Μακεδονία]]'' (Makedonia) was named after ''[[Μακεδών]]'' (Makedon), the [[patriarch]] of the Macedonians.

